  ${
    $d f y t x i $.
    $( Note: does the intersection gives us the coarsest topology? Yes by
       iinss and inttop3 . It works with an empty family. The topology is
       { (/) } . $)
    $( The product topology of a family ` f ` of topologies is the coarsest
       topology over the product of the underlying sets that makes the
       projections continuous.  (Bourbaki TG I.14 ex. 3) Experimental. $)
    df-prtop $a |- topX = { <. f , y >. | ( f : dom f --> Top /\
       y = |^| { t e. Top | (
       U. t = X_ x e. dom f U. ( f ` x ) /\ A. i e. dom f
         ( X_ x e. dom f U. ( f ` x ) pr i ) e. ( t Cn ( f ` i ) ) ) } ) } $.
  $}

